// @run
// @log 1
// @warning Unreachable code
// Newlines are SOFT statement boundaries, so `return 1 print(9)` is two
// statements — `return 1` then `print(9)` — NOT a bare `return` followed by a
// stray expression. The trailing statement is dead code (flagged by the
// unreachable-code lint), but it must not be mistaken for the function's
// implicit return value: with an annotated `i32` return that previously
// surfaced a spurious `expected i32, got null` type error. The `return`'s
// expression (`1`) is the value, which `print(early())` logs.
function early(): i32 { return 1 print(9) }
print(early())
